A former Super Eagles player, Justice Christopher, has been reported dead. The former midfielder was said to have battled high blood pressure. He reportedly slumped in his hotel in Gwolshe, off Tudun Wada Ring Road, Jos, Plateau State, on Wednesday. The former Nigerian player was said to be full of life, showing no sign of health challenge when he was seen in company with his friends on Tuesday. His remains were said to have been deposited at the Plateau Specialists Hospital morgue. An autopsy is expected to be carried out on his corpse. 